    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa">
                <!--This poem appears sideways on the facs (left to right from bottom to top), and the ink appears to be an brownish-orangish color-->
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="print" medium="ink-brown"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/><hi rend="caps">THE MEUSE</hi><lb/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/><unclear reason="erased" resp="#KCM">The Meuse</unclear></head>
                <lg type="stanza" n="1">
                    <l><handShift script="cursive"/>The sky was clear, the morn was gay</l>
                    <l>In promise of a cloudless day <add rend="linenumber-right-JR">175</add></l>
                    <l>Fresh flew the breeze with whose light wing</l>
                    <l>Aspen and oak were quivering</l>
                    <l>From floweret dank it dashed the dew</l>
                    <l>The harebell bent its blossom blue</l>
                    <l>And from the <geogName corresp="#MEUSE">Meuse</geogName> the mist wreaths<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="the_meuse_glosses_contextual.php#MISTWREATHSGLOSS"/> grey<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">180</add></l>
                    <l>That morning breeze had swept away</l>
                    <l>Showing such scenes as well might seem</l>
                    <l>The fairy vision of a dream<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="the_meuse_glosses_contextual.php#FAIRYVISIONGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>For changing still and still as fair</l>
                    <l>Rock&#x2038;<add place="above"><space quantity="5" unit="chars"/>wave</add>and wood were mingled there<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">185</add></l>
                    <l><damage agent="fire"><supplied resp="#DCH">Peak</supplied> <unclear resp="#KCM">over peak, fantastic ever</unclear></damage><ref type="gloss_textual" target="the_meuse_poem_glosses_textual.php#DAMAGEGLOSS" /></l>
                    <l><damage agent="fire"><gap reason="burned" extent="several words"/></damage></l>
                    <!--recto column begins-->
                    <l>And grey and gaunt their lichened head</l>
                    <l>Rose sheerly from the rivers bed<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="the_meuse_glosses_contextual.php#PEAKOVERPEAKGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Whose mantling wave, in foamy sheet<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">190</add></l>
                    <l>Their stern projecting bases beat</l>
                    <l>And lashed to fury in his pride</l>
                    <l>In circling whirlpools swept the tide</l>
                    <l>And threatening on some future day</l>
                    <l>Those mighty rocks to tear away<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">195</add></l>
                    <l>What though their front should seem to be</l>
                    <l>A barrier to eternity<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="the_meuse_glosses_contextual.php#BARRIERGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>But on its side the cliffs between</l>
                    <l>Were mazy forests ever seen</l>
                    <l>That the tall cliffs steep flanks so grey</l>
                    <l>Were clothed in mantle green and gay</l>
                    <l>Long time along that <unclear resp="#DCH">d</unclear><ref type="gloss_textual" target="the_meuse_poem_glosses_textual.php#DGLOSS" /> dell so deep<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">202</add></l>
                    <l>Beside the rivers bed we sweep</l>
                    <l><damage agent="fire"><unclear resp="DCH">So steep</unclear></damage> the mighty crests inclined<ref type="gloss_textual" target="the_meuse_poem_glosses_textual.php#DAMAGE2GLOSS" /></l>
                    <!-- Sideways column begins -->
                    <l>None other pathway you might find<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">205</add></l>
                    <l>Till the tall cliffs gigantic grace</l>
                    <l>To undulating hills gave place</l>
                    <l>And vineyards clothe the bending brow</l>
                    <l>Stead of the clinging copsewood now</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
